    <h1>Welcome to DINGUS</h1>
    <p>This server provides comprehensive backend services for RFID-based access control systems.</p>
    
    <h2>What is DINGUS?</h2>
    <p>DINGUS (Deployable Integrated Network-Generalized User Selector) is HackPGH's access control solution. It is designed to integrate seamlessly with Wild Apricot API and numerous Wiegard26 RFID reader components.</p>

    <h2>Key Features</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Integration with Wild Apricot API & Webhooks for tag and training sign-off authorization.</li>
        <li>Persistent SQLite database synchronized with WA API every 30 minutes.</li>
        <li>Event-based sync: Webhook support for `Contact` and `Membership` Triggers</li>
        <li>Web UI configuration and management screens</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How to Use</h2>
    <p>You can check out the documentation available on the GitHub repository. The server can be configured and managed through this site.</p>

